diagnoses.label: Major neurocognitive disorder, unspecified
evidence_spans: The findings indicated multiple areas of cerebral dysfunction.
The clinical picture is consistent with a progressive dementia syndrome such as Alzheimer's disease.
significant deficits in verbal and visual memory, proper naming, category fluency and working memory
performances which were below expectations on tests of speed of reading, visual scanning, visual construction and clock drawing
well preserved intellectual functioning and orientation
significant deficits in verbal and visual memory
limited insight into the scope and magnitude of cognitive dysfunction
progressive dementia syndrome such as Alzheimer's disease

patient_summary: This 64 year old man has memory problems. He has had trouble remembering names, phone numbers, and events for a long time. He has had a neurological evaluation and an MRI of his brain. The evaluation showed that he has mild cognitive impairment. He has had some spells of lightheadedness and anxiety. He is Catholic priest.
